We can use the Pythagorean Theorem to write an equation for the circle.

The points (5, 8), (6, 7), (-1, 8), (-2, 7), (-1,0), (-2, 1) (5, 0), and (6, 1)
appear to be points on the circle and all make (x - 2)² + (y 4)² = 5² true.
The points (7,4), (-3, 4), (2, 9), and (2, -1) also make the equation true, as do
points whose coordinates are not integers.
